Hi Everyone,
in this i will tell you how to install HTTP package in ubuntu 

Unlike other linux versions ubuntu uses apache2 package to enabel http service

in the terminal sudo su (Lets you login as root)

Sudo apt install apache2 (prompt for password and type Y)

to check the version type: sudo apache2 -version

sudo ufw app list (Ubuntu Firewal Spec)

Available applications:
  Apache
  Apache Full
  Apache Secure
  OpenSSH
  
  sudo ufw allow 'apache Full'
  sudo ufw allow 'Apache'
  
  sudo ufw status
  
  Status Active
  
  Done..! Thank you
